<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="rise-n">rise <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /raɪz/    美 /raɪz/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-fall-ame-raise">1.★ <strong>上升；上涨；增长【反:fall】；加薪 (AmE raise)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The cost of living is <strong>on the rise</strong>.  
生活成本正在上涨。</p><footer>2011 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Only with hard work can you expect to get <strong>a pay rise</strong>. 
只有努力工作你才能指望得到加薪。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>兴起：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the rise of electronic commerce (e-commerce)  
电子商务的兴起</p><footer>2014 北京</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="give-rise-to">give rise to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[正式用语] 引起；导致 (尤指坏事)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This may give rise to prejudices of the educated against those with little knowledge of English.
这可能导致受过教育的人对那些不太懂英语的人产生偏见。</p><footer>2014 江苏书面表达改</footer></div></div>